# Toast feedback

All user-facing action results (success, error, info) must use the shared toast — not `alert()`, browser dialogs, or ad-hoc banners.

## Source of truth

- Hook: `useToast()` in `app/components/toast.tsx`
- UI: `<Toast toast={toast} onDismiss={dismissToast} />`
- Default duration: `4000` ms (`DEFAULT_DURATION_MS`)

## Show feedback

```typescript
import { Toast, useToast } from "@/app/components/toast";

const { toast, showToast, dismissToast } = useToast();

// success / error / default
showToast("Settings saved.", "success");
showToast("Could not save project.", "error");
showToast("Publish flow coming soon.");
```

Render `<Toast>` once per client component that calls `showToast`.

## Auto-dismiss & hover behavior

- Toast auto-hides after `durationMs` (default 4 s).
- Timer **pauses** while the pointer is over the toast (`onMouseEnter`).
- Timer **resumes** when the pointer leaves (`onMouseLeave`); if no time remains, dismiss immediately.
- Do not reimplement this logic — extend `Toast` / `useToast` if behavior must change globally.

## Pointer & selection

- Over the toast block, cursor is **default** (`cursor-default`), not text/I-beam.
- Toast text is not selectable (`select-none`) — it is transient feedback, not copyable content.

## Variants

| Variant | Use when |
|---------|----------|
| `"success"` | Action completed |
| `"error"` | Action failed or validation blocked submit |
| `"default"` | Neutral info (e.g. coming soon) |

## Avoid

```typescript
// BAD
alert("Saved!");
window.confirm("Delete?");
<div className="fixed ...">Custom message</div>
```

Inline field errors next to inputs are fine for form validation; still use toast for submit/API outcomes.
